reviews.review: A great ending to the third trilogy and the whole series. A few challenges with pacing but more than compensated by the comedy, effects and the two leads.

I almost walked out of the movie if it wasn't for my wife literally holding me down. Rey is absolutely insane even holding a ship mid air while its all rdy heading to space lol and then even blows it right outta the sky that's when i was like i had enough within a 15 min span your jaw will absolutely drop is totally unbelievable basically put all the jedi powers into one person that's how it feels absolutely ridiculous. That's just one of the problems with it i don't want to give spoilers but save your money.

Jj trying to show us what his original vision is before rian came and ruin the show. For all the hate that rian is getting, does jj's version  proves to be better ? A reenactment of the original triology with new characters ? A definitve answer would be a firm no
Poor fanfic script with triple-A production value. SW's corpse is starting to smell.

Rise of Skywalker has a pretty bad ending from an outside perspective, but I think satisfying for most fans including me. It also delivers on the "fan service" part but also rushes on the story a bit too fast and leaves a few plot holes as a result.
The movie is really great, really good fanservice, the saga got the end it needed.
I really loved watching the movie

J.J. Abrams should be banned for Hollywood! Even my teenagers agreed with me that they should have stopped with the first three, classics. I just watched 6 Underground and it was made for Netflix, with three Times the vision, cinematography, acting and direction this movie had! Give me back my Money!

Wait for redbox, trust me you're not missing anything. At best you will find it mildly entertaining. As for me I thought the film in itself was rushed, full of plot holes, poorly developed characters, and overall nothing redeaming. As the finale to they Skywalker saga, if you will, it was an absolute travesty but oh well. FYI I did not pay to watch this I watched it for free overseas.
The movie is cool, exciting, full of references, but it is very similar to the return of jedi, doesn't innovate in the saga, Appeals a lot in the emotional and events of the classic trilogy
